# Cabin Comforts fleet — VPS crontab (Chicago box).  Install:  crontab crontab.example
# Times are server-local. The `auto` loop = pick clip -> build bed -> assemble 8h ->
# approve -> upload (private + jittered publishAt). One line per channel per run day.
#
# Put these in the cron environment (e.g. an .env the box loads, or here):
#   YT_RAINCABIN_REFRESH_TOKEN=...      (per-channel YouTube refresh tokens)
#   FREESOUND_API_KEY=...               (only needed when (re)stocking audio)
#   # YT_SLEEP_REFRESH_TOKEN / YT_PETDOG_REFRESH_TOKEN for channels 2 & 3

REPO=/opt/cabin-comforts            # adjust to your checkout path
PY=$REPO/venv/bin/python3           # the venv python

# --- the zero-touch loop: 3 distinct videos/week, jittered, staggered by channel ---
# Cabin Comforts (rain/storm/snow). Mon/Wed/Fri, off-peak.
40 4 * * 1,3,5  cd $REPO && $PY -m faceless_fleet.pipeline.run auto rain_cabin --publish >> /var/log/cabin.log 2>&1
# (Channels 2 & 3 once they exist — different days/times so no bulk-publish.)
# 20 5 * * 2,6   cd $REPO && $PY -m faceless_fleet.pipeline.run auto sleep_ambient   --publish >> /var/log/sleep.log 2>&1
# 10 6 * * 3,0   cd $REPO && $PY -m faceless_fleet.pipeline.run auto pet_calming_dogs --publish >> /var/log/pet.log 2>&1

# --- audio: re-stock occasionally for variety (optional) ---------------------------
# 0 3 1 * *  cd $REPO && $PY -m faceless_fleet.pipeline.run fetch-sfx --count 3 >> /var/log/cabin.log 2>&1

# NOTE: the clip library (assets/clips/<channel>/) is stocked in batches separately
# (Claude/Cowork generate + download). The loop above just consumes it.
